              "id": "b",
              "text": "4,000 lb"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "3,000 lb"
            },
            {
              "id": "d",
              "text": "1,500 lb"
            }
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "c",
          "explanation": "Load per leg = Total Load ÷ Number of Loaded Legs → 6,000 ÷ 2 = 3,000 lb."
        },
